{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584938","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584938"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:00:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:00:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14835"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14835","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14835"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.46,0.03,0.38,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7526"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114897"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7526","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7526"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14835"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96903"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5090"},{"type":"tags","id":"7879"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18407"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18551"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114897","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114897"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe fibrinolytic system is responsible for breaking down blood clots to maintain vascular patency.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the primary substrate for plasmin?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Tissue plasminogen activator","Plasminogen","Alpha2-antiplasmin","Fibrin","Urokinase"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFibrin\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary substrate for plasmin. Plasmin is a proteolytic enzyme that breaks down fibrin in blood clots into soluble fibrin degradation products, a process known as fibrinolysis. This is crucial for maintaining normal blood flow and preventing excessive clot formation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETissue plasminogen activator\u003C/strong\u003E converts plasminogen to plasmin but is not a substrate for plasmin. \u003Cstrong\u003EPlasminogen\u003C/strong\u003E is the inactive precursor of plasmin, not its substrate. \u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha2-antiplasmin\u003C/strong\u003E inhibits plasmin activity but is not its substrate. \u003Cstrong\u003EUrokinase\u003C/strong\u003E activates plasminogen to plasmin but is not a substrate for plasmin. Understanding this relationship between plasmin and fibrin is essential for comprehending both normal haemostasis and pathological thrombotic conditions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Plasmin is a proteolytic enzyme that breaks down fibrin into fibrin degradation products.","Fibrin is the main substrate for plasmin in the fibrinolytic system.","The fibrinolytic system helps maintain vascular patency by breaking down blood clots."],"references":["Kitchens, C. S., Konkle, B. A., \u0026 Kessler, C. M. (2013). Consultative Hemostasis and Thrombosis: Expert Consult-Online and Print. Elsevier Health Sciences","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., Fausto, N., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (2014). Robbins and Cotran pathologic basis of disease, professional edition e-book. Elsevier health sciences","Chaudhry R, Usama SM, Babiker HM. Physiology, Coagulation Pathways. [Updated 2023 Aug 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482253/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96903"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14835"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":